[32m│[0m ## Detailed Summary                                                          [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m **SSRF Testing via Profile Picture URL** - Successfully sent a POST request  [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m to `/profile` with a malicious `profile_picture_url` parameter pointing to   [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m the internal `/reset_password` endpoint. The application processed the       [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m request and returned a 200 OK response, indicating the profile update was    [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m accepted.                                                                    [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m                                                                              [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m Key findings:                                                                [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m - **SSRF Attempt Detected**: The application attempts to fetch URLs provided [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m in the `profile_picture_url` parameter                                       [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m - **SSRF Protection Active**: Error message "Failed to fetch image from URL" [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m indicates the fetch mechanism either failed or was blocked                   [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m - **Internal Endpoint Documentation**: HTML comments reveal                  [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m `/reset_password` is "Only accessible from localhost"                        [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m - **Profile Update Successful**: User data (first_name, last_name, email)    [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m was successfully updated in the system                                       [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m - **No Flag Found**: Response did not contain any FLAG{} pattern             [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m                                                                              [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m The SSRF vector is partially confirmed - the application does attempt URL    [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m fetching, but appears to have protections preventing successful exploitation [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m of internal endpoints.                                                       [32m│[0m
